# Shell scripts MUST keep LF line endings. They run on NFSN's FreeBSD via
# /bin/sh; a CRLF makes the kernel fail to find the interpreter ("bad
# interpreter: No such file or directory"). Committing from Windows
# (core.autocrlf=true) would otherwise risk CRLF creeping in and silently
# breaking the embed cron tick / heartbeat.
*.sh text eol=lf
